# docs/done.log — append-only completion record for FIXES.md items
#
# Format (post-FIX-159, 5 columns):
#   ISO-DATE | FIX-ID | commit-sha | verified | note
#     ISO-DATE     yyyy-mm-dd of completion
#     FIX-ID       matches <!--id:FIX-NNN--> marker in docs/FIXES.md
#     commit-sha   short SHA of the commit that completed it, or "backfill", or "reopen"
#     verified     local-only | prod-only | local+prod | unverified
#                  Sourced from a `Verified:` commit trailer; defaults to "unverified" when absent.
#     note         short human-readable description
#
# Legacy 4-column rows (pre-FIX-159) are read as `verified=unverified`.
#
# Rules:
#   - APPEND ONLY. Never rewrite or reorder existing lines.
#   - Generated by `pnpm fixes:sync` from `Fixes:` and `Verified:` trailers in commit messages.
#   - Safe to hand-append for historical backfills; the sync script deduplicates by (FIX-ID, sha).
#   - If an item is reopened, add a new `reopen` line instead of deleting the original:
#       2026-04-20 | FIX-042 | reopen | unverified | graph regression on production; reverting check
#     (reopen handling is not yet automated — hand-uncheck FIXES.md if needed, sync script preserves that.)
#   - `grep "| prod-only |"  done.log` surfaces items shipped without local repro.
#   - `grep "| unverified |" done.log` surfaces items where the trailer was forgotten — useful to audit.
#
# See CLAUDE.md "FIXES Workflow" section for the full protocol.

